    "abstract": "This article introduces a paradigm for the calculation of an alternative solution to Nash equilibrium applicable to the class of games, that we call \u201dG\u201d, and develops mathematical methods for the analysis of such games. The concepts of deterrence, equilibrium and temporized solution will be introduced by means of mathematical de nitions. The main result is the demonstration of the existence of the equilibrium point for every game G, while other results concern the geometrical structure of the solution and the restriction to symmetrical games in order to create a rigorous characterization of such situations. The topics that will be discussed have a signi cance that goes beyond the mere mathematics discussion to attain a level of universal understanding that aims to describe some of the most profound aspects of human society, religion, politics and in some ways, of consciousness itself. Date: December, 2007. 1 ar X iv :0 80 6. 13 43 v3 [ cs .G T ] 2 1 Se p 20 08",
